result.text:
The Shengli Street is one of #Wenchang's important #landmarks. It was built in 1895 by overseas Chinese originally from Hainan in Southeast Asia, and has 176 Nanyang-style arcades. In 2019, as Haiwen Bridge was opened to traffic, Puqian Town re-planned and renovated the old street. Locals have therefore benefited from an optimised living environment and a more convenient traffic within the vicinity.
#culture #HistoricArchitecture
